HEADWORD: De bene esse
<hw>De be"ne es"se</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Of well being; of formal sufficiency for the time;
conditionally; provisionally.</def> <rj><au>Abbott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
